            <div class="project-section">
                <h2>Overview</h2>
                <p>4SeamMetrics is an ambitious baseball analytics platform that represents the intersection of my two greatest passions: data science and baseball. This project aims to transform how we analyze and understand baseball through advanced statistical modeling, real-time data processing, and AI-powered insights.</p>
                <p>Currently in the research phase, I'm evaluating various baseball APIs, designing the database architecture, and planning the integration of large language models to provide natural language queries and insights that make complex baseball statistics accessible to everyone—from casual fans to professional scouts.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="project-section">
                <h2>Project Vision</h2>
                <p>The goal of 4SeamMetrics is to create a comprehensive baseball analytics ecosystem that:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Democratizes Advanced Stats:</strong> Makes sabermetrics and advanced metrics accessible through intuitive visualizations and natural language explanations</li>
                    <li><strong>Enables Real-Time Analysis:</strong> Processes live game data to provide in-the-moment insights and predictions</li>
                    <li><strong>Powers Custom Models:</strong> Allows users to build and test their own statistical models using historical data</li>
                    <li><strong>Integrates AI Workflows:</strong> Uses LLMs to answer complex baseball questions and generate detailed analytical reports</li>
                    <li><strong>Scales Efficiently:</strong> Handles massive datasets spanning decades of baseball history using cloud infrastructure</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="project-section">
                <h2>Planned Technology Stack</h2>
                <div class="tech-stack">
                    <span class="tech-badge">Python</span>
                    <span class="tech-badge">Baseball APIs</span>
                    <span class="tech-badge">LLM Integration</span>
                    <span class="tech-badge">Cloud Infrastructure</span>
                    <span class="tech-badge">Statistical Modeling</span>
                    <span class="tech-badge">Data Pipelines</span>
                    <span class="tech-badge">React</span>
                    <span class="tech-badge">Data Visualization</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="project-section">
                <h2>Key Features in Development</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>API Integration:</strong> Evaluating MLB Stats API, Retrosheet, Baseball Reference, and FanGraphs for comprehensive data coverage</li>
                    <li><strong>Custom Statistical Models:</strong> Building proprietary metrics that go beyond traditional sabermetrics</li>
                    <li><strong>LLM-Powered Insights:</strong> Natural language interface for querying player stats, game situations, and historical trends</li>
                    <li><strong>Predictive Analytics:</strong> Machine learning models for game outcomes, player performance projections, and injury risk</li>
                    <li><strong>Interactive Dashboards:</strong> Real-time visualizations of player metrics, team performance, and league-wide trends</li>
                    <li><strong>Historical Database:</strong> Comprehensive archive of baseball statistics dating back over a century</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="project-section">
                <h2>Research Phase</h2>
                <p>I'm currently in deep research mode, focusing on:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Evaluating different baseball data APIs for reliability, coverage, and cost</li>
                    <li>Designing a scalable database schema to handle millions of data points</li>
                    <li>Prototyping LLM integration for natural language baseball queries</li>
                    <li>Studying advanced sabermetrics and statistical methodologies</li>
                    <li>Planning cloud infrastructure for efficient data processing</li>
                    <li>Researching existing baseball analytics platforms to identify gaps and opportunities</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="project-section">
                <h2>Why This Project Matters to Me</h2>
                <p>4SeamMetrics isn't just a portfolio piece—it's a long-term passion project that will evolve alongside my data science career. Baseball has always been a numbers game, and as analytics continue to revolutionize the sport, I want to contribute tools and insights that push the boundaries of what's possible.</p>
                <p>This project allows me to apply everything I'm learning in my Master's program—from statistical modeling and machine learning to cloud architecture and data engineering—while working on something I genuinely love. It's the perfect intersection of passion and practice, and I don't see myself ever stopping work on it.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="project-section">
                <h2>Timeline</h2>
                <p>This is a long-term, evolving project with no fixed completion date. As I grow my skillset and the field of data science advances, 4SeamMetrics will continue to incorporate new technologies, methodologies, and insights. Current focus is on completing the research phase and building a minimum viable product (MVP) for initial testing.</p>
